node.text:
The making of Gillian Anderson’s dress for the 2021 Met Gala at the @metmuseum, designed by Gabriela Hearst and created bespoke in the Chloé ateliers in Paris. 

A charcoal grey dress in repurposed organic silk crepe with a halter neckline. At its centre, an ammonite nautilus shell is incorporated seamlessly into the dress using hand-knotted macrame techniques.

Ammonites lived during the periods of Earth history known as the Jurassic and Cretaceous. Together, these represent a time interval of about 140 million years.

#MetGala #MetInAmerica

node.text:
Final touches ahead of the 2021 Met Gala at the @metmuseum: Gillian Anderson’s made-to-measure, charcoal grey dress, designed by Gabriela Hearst, was created in the Chloé ateliers from repurposed, organic silk crepe and features an ammonite nautilus shell seamlessly incorporated with hand-knotted macramé techniques.

Gabriela chose a chalk white nappa leather dress with perforated scallops from her #ChloeAW21 show.

#MetGala #MetInAmerica

node.text:
Gillian Anderson and Gabriela Hearst attended the 2021 Met Gala at the @metmuseum in celebration of In America: A Lexicon of Fashion and the 75th anniversary of the #CostumeInstitute. 

Both in Chloé, Gillian wore a made-to-measure dress in repurposed, organic silk crepe with an ammonite nautilus shell – seamlessly integrated by hand-knotted macramé techniques – at its centre. Gabriela wore a chalk white nappa leather dress with perforated scallops from the #ChloeAW21 show.

#MetGala #MetInAmerica
